06/08/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Foreign Minister Miodrag Vlahovic asked the OSCE's Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights (ODIHR) to send observers to next month's parliamentary elections, the newspaper Pobeda reported on Saturday (5 August).
Vlahovic sent a letter of request to Christian Strohal -- the head of ODIHR in Warsaw.
Both parliamentary and local elections are scheduled for 10 September, the first since Montenegro's split from Serbia in May.
(Focus news agency -- 05/08/06)
